<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 94 / DTI helps to finance late payments to construction industry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Department of Trade and Industry is helping to finance measures to
combat late payment in the construction industry, Andrew Taylor writes.
The department is giving Pounds 30,000 to the Federation of Master Builders,
which yesterday launched a code of practice for its 17,500 members to
encourage them and their customers to pay on time.
The federation provides a telephone hot-line to members seeking legal advice
on how to recover money they are owed. It also offers a credit check service
in association with Infocheck, which allows companies to investigate the
payment record of prospective employers, main contractors and
sub-contractors.
Under the voluntary code of practice, members will be expected to agree
payment terms before signing contracts and honour these agreements.
Lord Strathclyde, minister for small businesses, welcomed the code and urged
other trade bodies to follow the federation's example. The grant runs until
November.
</TEXT>
