FT  17 JAN 94 / Business Travel: Dearer France - Travel Update
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Travellers to France face a series of price hikes on cigarettes, petrol and
telephone calls, leaving almost no one in the country exempt.
From this month, smokers will have to pay 13 per cent more for cigarettes
and tobacco on Monday, petrol is up by 2.3 per cent, and domestic telephone
calls will be invoiced on the basis of a three-minute chat, instead of the
previous six-minute base rate.
