<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JAN 94 / NHS cleaners covered by Tupe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The contracting-out of National Health Service cleaning work to private
companies is covered by the European Union's transfer regulations, which
protect the pay and conditions of workers for at least one year, according
to a Liverpool industrial tribunal.
Following an Employment Appeals Tribunal ruling in another case last year it
had been assumed that the Transfer of Undertakings, Protection of Employment
(Tupe) regulations would not generally apply to NHS cleaning. But the latest
judgment, which concerned contracting out at Walton Hospital to Taylorplan
Services, has ruled that it is covered by Tupe.
