of England in an attempt to cut its waiting lists, but apparently they all
refused.
Mr Straw said yesterday: 'The public have a right to know how much of
Shirley Porter's work was with the complicity, connivance and support of
senior national Tories and how far they were simply content to turn a blind
eye or deaf ear to what was going on.'
