FT  17 JAN 94 / World News in Brief: European monetary system
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The D-Mark lost ground last week in the EMS grid as speculation persisted
that the Bundesbank might cut interest rates at its meeting this Thursday.
The weaker tone was aggravated by the strong runs by the dollar and sterling
against the D-Mark. The Dutch guilder strengthened its position while the
French and Belgian francs weakened.
