FT  15 JAN 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Income tax query
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I wonder if you would be good enough to set out for me, step by step, the
income tax calculation for 1993/94 assuming one has a salary of Pounds
20,000, investment (equities gross) of Pounds 10,000, a gross income of
Pounds 30,000, and one is under 65 and married.
It is the treatment of the married couples allowance at 20 per cent which
has perplexed me. I might add that I phoned the Revenue Enquiry Room for an
explanation but they 'regretted that they had no instructions yet'.
The restriction of relief on the married couple's allowance to 20 per cent
does not come into effect until 1994-95; it will be restricted to 15 per
cent for 1995-96.
